POLOKWANE – Cold to mild conditions are expected in the city this week, according to People’s Weather’s forecast. Temperatures will remain in the mid to high teens for the rest of the week, peaking at 20ºC on Sunday and next week Monday (June 6).  Wednesday (June 1) will be the coldest day of the week at 17ºC, while Sunday will peak at 20ºC. Single digit minimum temperatures are expected with a low of 6ºC on Wednesday, Thursday and Friday and peak at 9ºC this morning (May 31). The week will start off with partly cloudy conditions but will clear by this afternoon with sunny conditions to remain for the rest of the week. 